Content: "paper wallets" are nothing more than a priv key; however, even if you ascribe to the notion of the claim that it's "physical" because it's physically written down on a tangible object, it's still not "physical BTC" because it's a controlling ownership code for some BTC amount and not actual BTC (a paper wallet that has the priv key for an address that has 1000000 BTC is physically indistinguishable from a paper wallet that has the priv key for an address that has 0 BTC)
